defaultKAREN MAYdefaultASSOCIATE SOLICITORdefaultJOHN FORD SOLICITORS defaultTransforming Legadefaultl Aid Consultation: ResponsedefaultI make this response as solicitor who acted as a Local Authority solicitor for four years before becoming a legal aid solicitor in 1999.  I therefore have experience of representing the public sector as well as individual claimants (with the benefit of leg
defaultal aid) in Judicial Review cases.  I know the importance of Judicial Review as a way of there being public scrutiny of important public sector decisions.  I do not believe that the proposals are workable, for the following reasons: 
